  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nHi, \r\nDuring writing my test script I observed to many request of eth_getTransactionByHash to my fork provider.\r\nAfter looking at code [here](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/9d64f1fbc47d20f30c91e71c4560fd5b11d65a21/anvil/src/eth/api.rs#L901) and [here](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/cbf77c251f9bab770ab0114bd6bda6f47049b388/anvil/src/eth/backend/mem/mod.rs#L1660) it is look like that in case of pending transaction anvil will perform request to provider at any case\r\nIs it possible or to change order to query fork provider after checking pending transaction?\r\n\r\n10x",
